<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you buy some shares of a public company, an=
d you use your rights as a fairly tiny shareholder to call a shareholder me=
eting to replace the chief executive officer of the company, and nobody sho=
ws up to the meeting but you, and you vote your shares to replace the CEO w=
ith yourself, and then you send all of the company=E2=80=99s money to yours=
